      <h2 data-bk-layout="pad:trl" class="font-xl">{{ title }}</h2>

      <div data-bk-layout="palm:9 hands:8 lap:7" class="rte">
        <p class="font-m">Basekit's grid system is a faux-grid built on CSS <em>inline-block</em> and uses the <em>data</em> attribute rather than classes.</p>

        <p>Once white space has been removed, inline-block provides the flexibility and robustness that floats do not. Inline-block items can be vertically aligned and flow more consistently.</p>

        <p>The data attribute allows us to almost fully separate the layout styles from other CSS and classes.</p>
      </div>

